<section id="how-it-works" class="section pipeline-section" aria-labelledby="pipeline-heading">
  <div class="section-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Capture - Wiki - Inject</p>
    <h2 id="pipeline-heading">Capture → Wiki → Inject</h2>
    <p>
      Capture is slow and off the hot path. Inject is fast and happens before the agent acts.
      The separation is the architecture.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="pipeline-wrap">
    <aside class="pipeline-rail" aria-label="Pipeline rail">
      <a href="#capture-panel">Capture</a>
      <a href="#wiki-panel">Wiki</a>
      <a href="#inject-panel">Inject</a>
      <a href="#evals">Evaluate</a>
    </aside>

    <div class="pipeline-grid">
      <article id="capture-panel" class="pipeline-panel surface is-cyan">
        <div class="panel-index">01</div>
        <p class="eyebrow">◆ Capture</p>
        <h3>Turn completed sessions into cited claims.</h3>
        <p>
          At session end, pc reads the transcript and extracts atomic claims: decisions,
          constraints, corrections, open questions, and changes of direction. The model points
          at transcript line ranges. Rust slices the evidence.
        </p>
        <p class="microcopy">The model proposes evidence. Rust verifies it.</p>
        <div class="badge-row">
          <span class="badge is-blue">explicit</span>
          <span class="badge is-green">verified</span>
          <span class="badge is-amber">line-anchored</span>
        </div>
        <div class="line-snippet" aria-label="Line-numbered transcript excerpt">
          <span><b>128</b> user: No, not generic memory.</span>
          <span><b>129</b> user: Preserve provenance. The correction is the asset.</span>
          <span><b>130</b> assistant: Understood, position around cited human discernment.</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article id="wiki-panel" class="pipeline-panel surface is-green">
        <div class="panel-index">02</div>
        <p class="eyebrow">⬡ Wiki</p>
        <h3>Distill messy conversation into durable project knowledge.</h3>
        <p>
          Claims become a project wiki: guides for current truth, episode cards for direction
          changes, research records for investigations, and an append-only claim log underneath it all.
        </p>
        <p class="microcopy">A wiki, not a landfill.</p>
        <div class="badge-row">
          <span class="badge is-green">current</span>
          <span class="badge is-amber">historical</span>
          <span class="badge is-magenta">append-only</span>
        </div>
        <div class="artifact-stack" aria-label="Wiki artifact folders">
          <code>docs/wiki/guides/project-positioning.md</code>
          <code>docs/wiki/episodes/context-dump-reversal.md</code>
          <code>docs/wiki/research/inject-redesign-validation.md</code>
          <code>claims.jsonl</code>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article id="inject-panel" class="pipeline-panel surface is-magenta">
        <div class="panel-index">03</div>
        <p class="eyebrow">✎ Inject</p>
        <h3>Push the right context before the agent acts.</h3>
        <p>
          On each prompt, pc retrieves candidate sources, selects the relevant guides and episode
          cards, compiles a dense cited briefing, deduplicates against what the session has already
          seen, and injects the result as a system reminder.
        </p>
        <p class="microcopy">Context window is attention.</p>
        <div class="badge-row">
          <span class="badge is-blue">selected</span>
          <span class="badge is-cyan">deduped</span>
          <span class="badge is-magenta">injected</span>
        </div>
        <div class="trace-block" aria-label="Inject trace">
          <span>TITLE: Relevant project direction</span>
          <span>The product is positioned around cited human discernment,</span>
          <span>not generic memory. (docs/wiki/guides/positioning.md:18)</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
